{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/art-of-travel-module-c","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you’re doing Module C Elective 2 then you’ll need to think about Alain de Botton. This guy has read a lot of books and knows just about everything there is to know about the most obscure philosophers/thinkers/writers/dudes in Europe and beyond.</p>\n<p>His emphasis is the search for happiness and he loves to ask: ‘Why?’</p>\n<p>He’s easy to read too – witty, insightful and thought-provoking. Like any good writer, he knows how to identify and then explore irony.</p>\n<p>But why does he write about travel and how does he use language to represent his thoughts and ideas?</p>\n<p>YouTube video: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kETN114A4IE\">Alain de Botton: The Art of Travel</a></p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/art-of-travel-module-c","title":"The Art of Travel - Module C Elective 2","author":"Mathew Teakle","date":"08 June, 2015","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/0f5878524933d46cc9bdd227cc1a8a70/f5ad6/travel-map.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0f5878524933d46cc9bdd227cc1a8a70/740c5/travel-map.jpg 235w,\n/static/0f5878524933d46cc9bdd227cc1a8a70/1a7ba/travel-map.jpg 470w,\n/static/0f5878524933d46cc9bdd227cc1a8a70/f5ad6/travel-map.jpg 940w,\n/static/0f5878524933d46cc9bdd227cc1a8a70/10d63/travel-map.jpg 1080w","sizes":"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px"}}},"featuredImage_alt":"world map, camera and passport"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}